sentences: Finn Sletten (born 11 August 1952) is a Norwegian jazz musician (drums and percussions).
After a study tour to Arizona (1968–70), he played in his home town with such musicians as Paul Weeden Band at Festival of North Norway (1972) and an album (1974).

Sletten was at the Festival of North Norway 2009 awarded Stubøprisen to have been "a significant pioneer and inspiration to generations of north Norwegian jazz musicians".
That same year he also received the prestigious Gammleng-prisen in the class jazz by "Fond for utøvende kunstnere".
